OL,6,FHowever this means that more          
OL,7,Fadvertising than normal is now being  
OL,8,Fshown.                                
OL,10,FThe Code on the Scheduling of         
OL,11,FTelevision Advertisements allows for  
OL,12,Fthe transfer of lost advertising time 
OL,13,Fin certain circumstances. This is just
OL,14,Fsuch a situation.                     
OL,16,FThe broadcasters will have approached 
OL,17,FOfcom with a request to do this.      
OL,19,FThe temporary increase in advertising 
OL,20,Fis particularly noticeable on ITV.    
OL,3,CCommercial channels play catch-up with
OL,4,Cadverts                               
OL,22,                                   G2/6
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
