OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F343A1664222673
OL,6,FThe decision is not a given  there is
OL,7,Fa risk that an increase in advertising
OL,8,Ftime could drive down prices so be of 
OL,9,Fno benefit to broadcasters or viewers.
OL,10,FThat will need proper examination.    
OL,12,FIt doesn't go without saying that a   
OL,13,Fpermanent increase would be handled in
OL,14,Fthe same way on air. Programme        
OL,15,Fdurations may need to be slightly     
OL,16,Freduced to help keep the schedule     
OL,17,Frunning to time.                      
OL,19,FOfcom's current consultation runs for 
OL,20,Fanother fortnight.                    
